00:25:33.440 --> 00:25:37.110
these brands
and tell them I've been working and I know

00:25:37.110 --> 00:25:40.940
what's going
to be better for your brand -- I mean, not

00:25:40.940 --> 00:25:45.200
your brand but the people you want to reach.
Tell me who you want to reach on the Internet

00:25:45.200 --> 00:25:47.930
and I'll
tell you what's the best way for us to do

00:25:47.930 --> 00:25:51.670
this and to do
that. And they're very happy usually because

00:25:51.670 --> 00:25:56.110
this is so
new that, you know, you have to be, like,

00:25:56.110 --> 00:25:58.870
now of course I
see young people coming out. I want to work

00:25:58.870 --> 00:26:01.680
on Internet
and everything. But three years ago people

00:26:01.680 --> 00:26:05.030
were like
working on Internet was not that good. You

00:26:05.030 --> 00:26:08.300
prefer to be
in a magazine. Now people really want to do

00:26:08.300 --> 00:26:10.880
it. So
there's still a lack. People are still looking

00:26:10.880 --> 00:26:15.060
for
advice and feedback. And when you have your

00:26:15.060 --> 00:26:17.290
veteran and [giggles]
you have so much experience, they listen to

00:26:17.290 --> 00:26:18.290
me.

00:26:18.290 --> 00:26:21.160
&gt;&gt;Presenter: So what sort of advice do you
give to a big brand.

00:26:21.160 --> 00:26:23.710
Something that you're not going to get paid
for. I don't

00:26:23.710 --> 00:26:28.630
want to take away from your consulting. [laughter]
What sort of big

00:26:28.630 --> 00:26:32.330
problem do they come to you with? You sort
of think

00:26:32.330 --> 00:26:33.330
through.

00:26:33.330 --> 00:26:37.790
&gt;&gt;Garance: A typical problem I think -- different
for every case.

00:26:37.790 --> 00:26:44.391
Most brands want to be cool and it's not easy.
So they

00:26:44.391 --> 00:26:48.000
want to be cool, but they don't want to change
the way

00:26:48.000 --> 00:26:53.280
they do. I think there are some brands who
-- you know,

00:26:53.280 --> 00:26:56.330
it's interesting. You have to develop like
new

00:26:56.330 --> 00:26:59.450
departments almost. You know, and I think
now there is

00:26:59.450 --> 00:27:04.710
very good things happening, like, for example
I look at Kate Spade's Tumblr, for example.

00:27:04.710 --> 00:27:07.670
It's interesting because they
really are able to tell. I think brands need

00:27:07.670 --> 00:27:11.250
to tell
their story and to make people dream like

00:27:11.250 --> 00:27:15.070
Ralph Lauren said.
He said, "I don't design dresses; I design

00:27:15.070 --> 00:27:17.290
dreams". People don't really care about. They
can find the same

00:27:17.290 --> 00:27:21.790
dress everywhere. And, you know, cheaper maybe.
And

00:27:21.790 --> 00:27:24.650
everything so I think when you go to a store
what you

00:27:24.650 --> 00:27:28.240
want is to buy a part of their cool and their
history and

00:27:28.240 --> 00:27:30.341
what they are and who represents them and
everything.

00:27:30.341 --> 00:27:33.200
And I think that's now taking care of a brand
is doing

00:27:33.200 --> 00:27:37.370
all of that. Even myself I start to think
of myself as a

00:27:37.370 --> 00:27:40.540
brand which feels very weird but you know
for a very long

00:27:40.540 --> 00:27:43.180
